<h1 style="font-size: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 20px;">The Immigrant Experience</h1>
<h2 style="font-size: 1.3em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 40px;">A Simulation of Housing Insecurity in Chicago</h2>

<hr style="margin: 30px 0;">

<div style="max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: left; font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6;">
<h3>Your Story</h3>
<p>You are an undocumented Guatemalan man in your early 20s living in Chicago. You have a wife and a one-year-old child, with another baby on the way.</p>

<p>You start with <strong>$900 in your bank account</strong> and <strong>no permanent housing</strong>. Through painting and odd jobs, you must:</p>

<ul style="margin: 20px 0;">
<li>Find and secure permanent housing for your family</li>
<li>Navigate bureaucratic delays and application denials</li>
<li>Balance work, income, and family needs</li>
<li>Make difficult choices under time pressure</li>
</ul>

<h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">About This Experience</h3>
<p>This simulation is based on real challenges faced by undocumented immigrants in Chicago:</p>

<ul style="margin: 20px 0;">
<li>Housing discrimination and documentation requirements</li>
<li>Income verification barriers and credit history gaps</li>
<li>Limited job opportunities and unstable employment</li>
<li>Time pressure and bureaucratic waiting periods</li>
<li>The constant weighing of risk versus necessity</li>
</ul>

<div class="status-box status-box-warning" style="margin: 20px 0;">
<strong>Content Notice:</strong> This game addresses themes of housing insecurity, financial stress, family pressure, and the difficulties faced by undocumented immigrants. The experience is designed to be educational and empathy-building.
</div>

<h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">Game Structure</h3>
<p>You will play day-by-day, making decisions about:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Work:</strong> Take jobs to earn money (but jobs take time)</li>
<li><strong>Transit:</strong> Buy CTA/Pace passes to reduce work time</li>
<li><strong>Housing:</strong> Apply to apartments (with varying approval chances)</li>
<li><strong>Family:</strong> Manage worries and maintain wellbeing</li>
</ul>

<p>Every decision has trade-offs. Applications take business days to process. Weekends feel like wasted time. The clock is always ticking.</p>
</div>

